cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.CL 

This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with recommender systems for music streaming services. It may also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category as it investigates listener behavior. Additionally, it could fall under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it discusses the explore/exploit framework commonly used in recommender systems. The paper also involves analyzing sequential data, which could place it in the Sequential Decision Making (cs.SD) sub-category. Finally, it may belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category as it deals with the sequencing of ads and songs in a listener's session.
